name: Marmota caligata
locality: Approximately 8 km west-northwest of Mt. Denson
occurrenceremarks: "Collected with .223 at 11:00am. One other marmot (juvenile) was observed, but not collected at the collection locality. An odd alarm call very similar to the "kee-ew" call made by Marmota vancouverensis was emitted in response to collector presence above the specimen. 5 pair mammae."
